@@ -0,0 +1,277 @@
+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner — petitioner registry, priority types, and petition helper APIs
+for dimension-driven writ scheduling. It governs which held writs (writs in
+`new` phase carrying `ext['reckoner']`) are approved, deferred, or declined,
+and exposes the ergonomic `petition()` / `withdraw()` helpers for petitioners.
+
+See also: [`docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md`](../../../docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md).
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+```sh
+pnpm add @shardworks/reckoner-apparatus
+```
+
+Register the apparatus in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": [
+    "@shardworks/clerk-apparatus",
+    "@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus"
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerApi {
+  petition(request: PetitionRequest): Promise<WritDoc>;
+  withdraw(writId: string, reason?: string): Promise<WritDoc>;
+  registeredSources(): ReadonlyMap<string, PetitionerDescriptor>;
+  reckonerConfig(): ResolvedReckonerConfig;
+}
+```
+
+### `petition(request)`
+
+Post a writ in `new` phase with `ext['reckoner']` set correctly.
+
+```typescript
+const reckoner = guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner');
+
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  type:    'mandate',
+  title:   'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:    '...',
+  codex:   'nexus',
+
+  source:   'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',
+  payload:    { /* opaque snapshot data */ },
+  labels:     { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' },
+});
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'] === { source, priority, complexity, payload, labels }
+```
+
+Steps performed:
+1. Validates `source` against the registry (per `enforceRegistration` config).
+2. Fills default values for any omitted `priority` dimensions.
+3. Validates all dimension values against the schema.
+4. Calls `clerk.post()` with the writ fields.
+5. Writes `writ.ext['reckoner']` via `clerk.setWritExt()`.
+
+All `priority` dimensions are optional in the request; omitted fields fall
+back to the contract defaults:
+
+| Dimension | Default |
+|---|---|
+| `visionRelation` | `'vision-neutral'` |
+| `severity` | `'minor'` |
+| `scope` | `'minor-area'` |
+| `time.decay` | `false` |
+| `time.deadline` | `null` |
+| `domain` | `[]` |
+
+### `withdraw(writId, reason?)`
+
+Cancel a held writ. Thin wrapper around `clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', ...)`.
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.withdraw(writ.id, 'Snapshot superseded by more recent drift.');
+```
+
+### `registeredSources()`
+
+Returns a read-only snapshot of the petitioner registry, keyed by source id.
+
+```typescript
+for (const [source, descriptor] of reckoner.registeredSources()) {
+  console.log(source, descriptor.description);
+}
+```
+
+### `reckonerConfig()`
+
+Returns the fully-resolved Reckoner configuration with defaults applied.
+
+```typescript
+const config = reckoner.reckonerConfig();
+// config.enforceRegistration: boolean  (default: false)
+// config.disabledSources: string[]     (default: [])
+```
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+| Field | Type | Default | Description |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `enforceRegistration` | `boolean` | `false` | When `true`, petitions from unregistered sources are cancelled. When `false`, a warning is logged but the writ is processed. |
+| `disabledSources` | `string[]` | `[]` | Sources in this list are skipped — writs are left in `new` phase, no reckoning entry written. Remove a source to resume consideration. |
+
+---
+
+## Kit Interface
+
+Kits and apparatus that emit Reckoner-gated writs declare their sources via
+the `petitioners` contribution:
+
+```typescript
+// In a plugin's kit or apparatus supportKit:
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+        description: 'Periodic vision-vs-reality snapshots emitted when ' +
+                     'the keeper observes drift worth surfacing.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+};
+```
+
+### `PetitionerDescriptor`
+
+```typescript
+interface PetitionerDescriptor {
+  /**
+   * Source id. Form: `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`.
+   * Examples: `vision-keeper.snapshot`, `patron-bridge.commission`.
+   * The `{pluginId}.` prefix must match the contributing plugin's id.
+   */
+  source: string;
+  /** One-liner describing what this petitioner emits. */
+  description: string;
+}
+```
+
+### Source-id grammar
+
+Source ids must be `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`:
+- Both the plugin-id prefix and the kebab suffix use lowercase letters,
+  digits, and hyphens.
+- Neither part may start or end with a hyphen.
+- No consecutive hyphens.
+- The prefix must match the contributing plugin's derived id.
+
+Malformed ids or wrong-prefix ids hard-fail at startup.
+
+### Collision policy
+
+Two `petitioners` entries with the same `source` string are a **hard startup
+error**. The Reckoner refuses to start with a diagnostic naming both
+contributing plugin ids — load order never silently resolves collisions.
+Mirrors the collision policy for Clerk writ-types, Spider rig-template-mappings,
+and Fabricator engine designs.
+
+---
+
+## Priority types
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation:
+    | 'vision-blocker'   // vision unreachable without this
+    | 'vision-violator'  // current state diverges from vision
+    | 'vision-advancer'  // pushes toward aspirational vision
+    | 'vision-neutral';  // doesn't touch the product vision
+  severity:
+    | 'critical'   // production breakage, agents fully blocked
+    | 'serious'    // significant ongoing degradation
+    | 'moderate'   // noticeable but tolerable
+    | 'minor';     // cosmetic, convenience, polish
+  scope:
+    | 'whole-product'  // every user / every guild
+    | 'major-area'     // a major feature or subsystem
+    | 'minor-area';    // a small slice, one workflow
+  time: {
+    decay:    boolean;       // true → urgency increases with time
+    deadline: string | null; // ISO date string, or null
+  };
+  domain: Array<DomainTag>;  // multi-valued classification
+};
+
+type DomainTag =
+  | 'security' | 'compliance' | 'cost' | 'feature' | 'quality'
+  | 'infrastructure' | 'documentation' | 'research' | 'ergonomics';
+
+type ComplexityTier =
+  | 'mechanical'    // ~50K–200K tokens
+  | 'bounded'       // ~200K–1M tokens
+  | 'exploratory'   // ~1M–5M tokens
+  | 'open-ended';   // ~5M+ tokens; omit when unsure
+```
+
+---
+
+## Helper functions
+
+The following helper functions are exported for consumers that need to work
+with priority types outside of `petition()`:
+
+```typescript
+/** Return the contract-specified default priority dimensions. */
+function defaultPriority(): Priority;
+
+/** Fill a partial priority with defaults for any omitted dimensions. */
+function fillPriorityDefaults(partial: Partial<Priority>): Priority;
+
+/** Validate all five priority dimensions; throws on any invalid value. */
+function validatePriority(priority: Priority): void;
+
+/** Validate a ComplexityTier string; throws when invalid. */
+function validateComplexity(complexity: ComplexityTier): void;
+
+/** Validate a source id for format conformance; throws on any violation. */
+function validateSourceId(source: string, contributingPluginId: string): void;
+```
+
+---
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- **Required:** `@shardworks/clerk-apparatus` — `petition()` calls
+  `clerk.post()` and `clerk.setWritExt()`; `withdraw()` calls
+  `clerk.transition()`.
+
+---
+
+## Behavior
+
+- **Kit-static registry.** Petitioner sources are consumed from `petitioners`
+  kit contributions during `start()` and sealed at `phase:started`. No
+  runtime registration after sealing.
+- **Permissive by default.** `enforceRegistration: false` (default) means
+  petitions from unregistered sources log a warning but are processed
+  normally. Set to `true` for strict production guilds.
+- **No scheduling logic here.** This apparatus posts writs in `new` phase
+  with `ext['reckoner']` populated. The CDC handler that watches held writs
+  and decides approve / defer / decline is a separate commission.
+- **`withdraw()` is a thin wrapper.** Calls `clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', ...)`.
+  No source-check — the wrapper exists for discoverability, not enforcement.
